        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): backfill provider.model in createWithAdapter when adapter returns empty string",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen `createWithAdapter` is called and the adapter returns an embedding\nresult with an empty `model` string, the search index stores the empty\nstring as the model identifier. This causes identity corruption in search\nresults where multiple embedding sources can't be distinguished.\n\n## Changes\n\n`extensions/memory-core/src/memory/embeddings.ts`: In `createWithAdapter`,\nbackfill `provider.model` from the adapter's configured model when the\nreturned model string is empty or undefined.\n\n`extensions/memory-core/src/memory/embeddings.test.ts`: Test coverage\nfor the backfill behavior.\n\n## Evidence\n\nVitest:\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/memory-core/src/memory/embeddings.test.ts\n```\n\n**Label**: bug\n\n_AI-assisted._",
